OL,3,CProposition to remove Jersey's Bailiff
OL,4,Cfrom States Assembly lodged
OL,6,FHowever, a 'Save the Bailiff of
OL,7,FJersey' social media account is
OL,8,Fprotesting the proposition.
OL,10,FCurrently, the Bailiff is a crown-
OL,11,Fappointed role responsible for the
OL,12,FStates Assembly's orderly conduct.
OL,14,FSimilar to the UK's Speaker of the
OL,15,FHouse, Sir Lindsay Hoyle, the Bailiff
OL,16,Fpresides over States proceedings, but
OL,17,Fcannot vote.
