OL,3,CProposition to remove Jersey's Bailiff
OL,4,Cfrom States Assembly lodged
OL,6,FDeputy Jehan proposes that the Bailiff
OL,7,Fcontinue as the Civic Head of Jersey
OL,8,Fand continue to swear in Members of
OL,9,Fthe States Assembly in the Royal Court.
OL,11,FUnder the proposition, the Bailiff
OL,12,Fwould also preside in the Assembly on
OL,13,FLiberation Day, on a Royal Visit, and
OL,14,Fbe invited to Preside in or address
OL,15,Fthe Assembly, on other ceremonial or
OL,16,Fappropriate occasions.
OL,18,FIn October, an anonymous account was
OL,19,Fcreated that preemptively called to
OL,20,Fstop any plans to remove Jersey's
OL,21,FBailiff from the States Assembly.
